  </title>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">In partnership with district governments and local communities in the Mara Region of Tanzania, PCI implements a three-year, USDA-funded Food for Education program to increase school enrollment, attendance, and performance for 70,000 children.  The main objectives of the program are to: a) Increase enrollment and attendance; b) Improve the health status of children; and c) Improve the learning environment for children.  Students receive a hot breakfast in over 100 schools on a daily basis.  Complementary activities implemented within the program include: teacher training; parent-teacher association (PTA) development and training; school garden construction; infrastructure improvements (including water and sanitation construction); health and hygiene activities; and the distribution of text books.</narrative>
